House Resolution 743
By: Representatives Hilton of the 48th, Jones of the 47th, and Gaines of the 120th
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending the State Government Affairs Council upon its 50th
2 anniversary; and for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, the State Government Affairs Council (SGAC) was established 50 years ago
4 with the mission to advance and support the state government affairs profession by fostering
5 community and relationship building with peers and elected officials, building knowledge,
6 and promoting diverse perspectives in a nonpartisan environment; and
7 WHEREAS, SGAC's members, consisting of government affairs professionals, have
8 consistently worked to enhance understanding and communication between the public and
9 private sectors, ensuring the fair representation of diverse interests; advocating for the
10 advancement of policies that promote unparalleled educational opportunities; providing a
11 forum for members and policymakers to convene and collaborate; mentoring the next
12 generation of state government affairs professionals; and promoting all aspects of diversity;
13 and
14 WHEREAS, through its collaboration with legislative bodies, administrative agencies, and
15 community stakeholders, SGAC has helped build a more responsive, transparent, and
16 accountable government at the state level; and
