17 WHEREAS, the 50th anniversary of SGAC represents a milestone of achievement and
18 service in its ongoing commitment to excellence in government affairs; and
19 WHEREAS, SGAC has fostered a forward-thinking platform for addressing emerging
20 challenges in state governance; and
21 WHEREAS, SGAC has created a legacy of fostering leadership, training, and advocacy that
22 has shaped the professional development of thousands of individuals in the field of
23 government relations.
24 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
25 the members of this body recognize and commend the State Government Affairs Council for
26 its 50 years of dedicated service and significant contributions to enhancing the relationship
27 between state and local governments, businesses, and communities.
28 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the members of this body encourage continued support
29 for the State Government Affairs Council's mission and commend its members for their
30 tireless work to advocate for sound policy decisions, transparency, and good governance.
31 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the members of this body extend congratulations to the
32 State Government Affairs Council and its members on reaching this remarkable milestone
33 as well as acknowledge their enduring influence on the state's government affairs landscape.
34 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
35 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to the
36 State Government Affairs Council.
